        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 3:32PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 332 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Niantic to near Stonington to White Oak.
Movement was east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Decatur, Taylorville, Mount Zion, Auburn, Rochester, Forsyth, Pawnee,
Moweaqua, Bement, Kincaid, Cerro Gordo, Harristown, Bethany, Long
Creek, Warrensburg, Divernon, Assumption, Blue Mound, Macon, and
Edinburg.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 55 between mile markers 77 and 86.
Interstate 72 between mile markers 115 and 148.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
